By Stella Kabruk  Kaduna  –  The Federal Ministry of Youth and Sports Development, North-West Zone says it is shocked by the demise of two members representing it on national Handball and Weightlifting Federation boards.Alhaji Abdullahi Idris, its Zonal Coordinator, who made the disclosure on Sunday in Kaduna, said the two members were Alhaji Ahmed Abubakar, on Handball Federation board and Alhaji Yahaya Mohammed on WeightLifting Federation.“The North-West Zonal Sports Office wishes to express its heart-felt condolences to the entire sporting communities over the demise of our two Zonal Representatives on Handball and Weightlifting Federation boards.“The shocking and sad events took place on the April 17 and April 18 respectively.”These condolences also extend to their immediate families, friends, the governments and people of Kaduna and Jigawa States,” he said said in a statement.Idris said that their individual contributions to the development of sports in the zone would be fondly missed, and would always be remembered.”May Allah grant them eternal rest and we, the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss Amen,” he prayed. (NAN) Kaduna - The President, Nigerian Handball Coach Association (NHCA), John Jatau, says arrangements have been concluded for the kick-off of 2016 Handball Premier League in Kaduna. Jatau made the disclosure at a news conference in Kaduna after a meeting of the NHCA executives from the six geological zones and representatives… April 1, 2016 In "Sports" Kaduna  -   Male and female teams drawn from Kano, Kaduna, Katsina, Sokoto, Kebbi, Zamfara and Jigawa states are being expected at the maiden edition of the North-West Zonal Under-17 Handball Competition. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the competition, being organised by the National Sports Commission (NSC),… February 25, 2016 In "Sports" By Millicent Ifeanyichukwu Lagos - Nigeria’s boxing legend, Obisa Nwakpa, has charged Lagos State Sports Commission (LSSC) to commence early prepa